    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\nusing namespace std;\n\nstruct TreeNode {\n  int val;\n  TreeNode *left, *right;\n  TreeNode(int v) : val(v), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n};\n\nint main() {\n  int n, p; cin >> n;\n  int vals[n];\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) cin >> vals[i];\n  TreeNode* nodes[n];\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) nodes[i] = new TreeNode(vals[i]);\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n    if (2*i+1 < n && vals[2*i+1] != -1) nodes[i]->left = nodes[2*i+1];\n    if (2*i+2 < n && vals[2*i+2] != -1) nodes[i]->right = nodes[2*i+2];\n  }\n  cin >> p;\n\n  // find successor\n\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "Inorder Successor in BST: the next node in inorder traversal. If the node has a right subtree, successor is the leftmost node in that right subtree. Otherwise, traverse from root tracking the last ancestor where we took a left turn.\n\nDiagram:\n      3\n     / \\\n    1   4\n     \\\n      2\n\nSuccessor of 2:\n  2 has no right child -> traverse from root:\n  3 > 2: record 3, go left\n  1 < 2: go right\n  2 == 2: stop\n  Last recorded ancestor (left turn): 3\n  Output: 3\n\nSuccessor of 4: no right child, traverse from root: 3 < 4 go right, 4 == 4, last recorded = none -> -1\n\nTime O(h), Space O(1).",
    complexity: {"time":"O(h)","space":"O(1)"},
    sheet: "Striver A2Z",
    solution_code: "TreeNode* target = nullptr; for (auto* n : nodes) if (n->val == p) { target = n; break; }\nif (!target) { cout << -1; return 0; }\nif (target->right) {\n  TreeNode* s = target->right;\n  while (s->left) s = s->left;\n  cout << s->val;\n} else {\n  TreeNode* succ = nullptr;\n  TreeNode* cur = nodes[0];\n  while (cur) {\n    if (p < cur->val) { succ = cur; cur = cur->left; }\n    else if (p > cur->val) cur = cur->right;\n    else break;\n  }\n  cout << (succ ? succ->val : -1);\n}",
