    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\nusing namespace std;\n\nstruct TreeNode {\n  int val;\n  TreeNode *left, *right;\n  TreeNode(int v) : val(v), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n};\n\nint rangeSum(TreeNode* root, int low, int high) {\n  if (!root) return 0;\n  if (root->val < low) return rangeSum(root->right, low, high);\n  if (root->val > high) return rangeSum(root->left, low, high);\n  return root->val + rangeSum(root->left, low, high) + rangeSum(root->right, low, high);\n}\n\nint main() {\n  int n, low, high; cin >> n;\n  int vals[n];\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) cin >> vals[i];\n  TreeNode* nodes[n];\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) nodes[i] = new TreeNode(vals[i]);\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n    if (2*i+1 < n && vals[2*i+1] != -1) nodes[i]->left = nodes[2*i+1];\n    if (2*i+2 < n && vals[2*i+2] != -1) nodes[i]->right = nodes[2*i+2];\n  }\n  cin >> low >> high;\n  cout << rangeSum(nodes[0], low, high) << endl;\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "Range Sum of BST uses the BST property to prune: if root.val < low, skip left subtree. If root.val > high, skip right subtree. Otherwise add root.val and recurse both sides.\n\nDiagram:\n      10\n     /  \\\n    5    15\n   / \\     \\\n  3   7     18\n\nRange [7, 15]:\n10 in [7,15] -> add 10 + rangeSum(left,7,15) + rangeSum(right,7,15)\n  left 5: 5<7 -> go right to 7: 7 in range -> add 7\n  right 15: 15 in range -> add 15 + go right to 18: 18>15 -> skip\nSum = 10+7+15 = 32\n\nTime O(n), Space O(n).",
