    test_cases: [{"input":"7\n1 2 3 4 5 6 7","expected":"12"}],
    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\nusing namespace std;\n\nstruct TreeNode {\n  int val;\n  TreeNode *left, *right;\n  TreeNode(int v) : val(v), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n};\n\nint sumRight(TreeNode* root, bool isRight) {\n  if (!root) return 0;\n  if (!root->left && !root->right && isRight) return root->val;\n  return sumRight(root->left, false) + sumRight(root->right, true);\n}\n\nint main() {\n  int n; cin >> n;\n  int vals[n];\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) cin >> vals[i];\n  TreeNode* nodes[n];\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) nodes[i] = new TreeNode(vals[i]);\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n    if (2*i+1 < n && vals[2*i+1] != -1) nodes[i]->left = nodes[2*i+1];\n    if (2*i+2 < n && vals[2*i+2] != -1) nodes[i]->right = nodes[2*i+2];\n  }\n  cout << sumRight(nodes[0], false) << endl;\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nsum-right-leaves:\n       1\n      / \\\n     2   3\n    / \\ / \\\n   4  5 6  7\n\n  Traverse with isRight flag:\n  1: not leaf, recurse left(false), right(true)\n    2(false): not leaf, recurse left(false), right(true)\n      4(false): leaf, not right → skip\n      5(true): leaf, right → add 5\n    3(true): not leaf, recurse left(true), right(true)\n      6(true): leaf, right → add 6\n      7(true): leaf, right → add 7\n\n  Sum = 5+6+7 = 18? Wait, right leaves are 5 and 7. 6 is a left child of 3.\n  Right leaves: 5(right of 2) + 7(right of 3) = 12\n```\nRecursive traversal with isRight flag. If leaf and isRight, add value. Time O(n), Space O(h).",
    complexity: {"time":"O(n)","space":"O(h)"},
