    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\n#include <queue>\nusing namespace std;\n\nstruct TreeNode {\n  int val;\n  TreeNode *left, *right;\n  TreeNode(int v) : val(v), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n};\n\nbool isSymmetric(TreeNode* a, TreeNode* b) {\n  if (!a && !b) return true;\n  if (!a || !b) return false;\n  return a->val == b->val && isSymmetric(a->left, b->right) && isSymmetric(a->right, b->left);\n}\n\nint main() {\n  int n; cin >> n;\n  int vals[n];\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) cin >> vals[i];\n  TreeNode* nodes[n];\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) nodes[i] = new TreeNode(vals[i]);\n  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n    if (2*i+1 < n && vals[2*i+1] != -1) nodes[i]->left = nodes[2*i+1];\n    if (2*i+2 < n && vals[2*i+2] != -1) nodes[i]->right = nodes[2*i+2];\n  }\n\n  // Check mirror symmetry\n\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nsymmetric-tree:\n      1\n     / \\\n    2   2\n   / \\ / \\\n  3  4 4  3\n\n  isSymmetric(1.left=2, 1.right=2):\n    2.val == 2.val ✓\n    isSymmetric(2.left=3, 2.right=3): 3==3 ✓, children null ✓ → true\n    isSymmetric(2.right=4, 2.left=4): 4==4 ✓, children null ✓ → true\n  → true\n\n  Asymmetric:\n    1\n   / \\\n  2   2\n   \\   \\\n    3   3\n  Right child of left != left child of right: 3 != null\n```\nRecursively check if left and right subtrees are mirrors: left.val == right.val, isSymmetric(left.left, right.right), isSymmetric(left.right, right.left). Also possible iteratively with queue. Time O(n), Space O(h).",
